==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Surreption
<hw>Sur*rep"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>surreptio</ets>, or <ets>subreptio</ets>. Cf.
<er>Subreption</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of
getting in a surreptitious manner, or by craft or stealth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fame by <qex>surreption</qex> got⟦br⟧
May stead us for the time, but lasteth not.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A coming unperceived or suddenly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surreptitious</ent>⟦br⟧
